@node "LFOFreqnc" "LFO Frequence"

    @{b}@{u}LFO Frequence@{uu}@{ub}

    There is a LFO (Low Frequence Oscillator), that affects to the speed of
    the modulation. Here you can alter the frequency.


@endnode

@node "LFODepth" "LFO phase modulation Depth"

    @{b}@{u}LFO phase modulation Depth@{uu}@{ub}

    Here you alter the phase modulations depth. In this case you alter  the
    effect density with this slider.

@endnode

@node "ChorFeedbLevl" "Feedback Level"

    @{b}@{u}Feedback Level@{uu}@{ub}

    Like in other effects you can here define how much of the effect  level
    should   come   back,   and   will   flow   another  once  through  the
    effectprocessor and will be "effected".

@endnode

@node "ChorDelayOffs" "Delay Offset"

    @{b}@{u}Delay Offset@{uu}@{ub}

    You can put a little time between the original sound and the 
    beginning of the effect.
@endnode

@node "ChorInput" "Input Mono Stereo"

    @{b}@{u}Input Mono Stereo@{uu}@{ub}

    It has only a small effect and depend on the sound you have choosen.

@endnode

