    Hear exactly ! 

    That has only a effect in the speed of the swinging in the upper-tones.
    Tha variance is small.

@endnode

@node "XGVFXSYMPHONICAUTOPAN" "Symphonic, Rotary Speaker, Tremolo, AutoPan"

    @{b}@{u}Symphonic, Rotary Speaker, Tremolo, AutoPan@{uu}@{ub}

    The effects:

    Symphonic     : a multi-phase version of celeste
    Rotary Speaker: simulation of rotary speakers
    Tremolo       : cyclical modulation (frequency & amplitude) of volume
    Auto Pan      : auto cyclical moving the sound image left<>right and/or
                    front<>back


    I  will  explain  in  alphabetical  order,  because  there   are   some
    differences between the labelorder in the different effects:

    Label       Real name
    ----------------------------------------------------------------------
    AM Depth    Amplitude Modulation Depth
    @{"DelayOffs" link "ChorDelayOffs" 0}   Delay Offset
    @{"Dry<->Wet" link "XGREVERBDRYWET" 0}   Balance between the original and the effect signal
    @{"EqLowFreq" link "EqLowFreq" 0}   Equalizer Low Frequence
    @{"EqLowGain" link "EqLowGain" 0}   Equalizer Low Frequence Gain
    @{"EqHigFreq" link "EqHigFreq" 0}   Equalizer Low Frequence
    @{"EqHigGain" link "EqHigGain" 0}   Equalizer Low Frequence Gain
    @{"F/R Depth" link "F/RDepth" 0}   Front to Rear distance (Depth)
    @{"LFOFreqnc" link "LFOFreqnc" 0}   Low Frequence Oscillator Frequence
    @{"LFODepth " link "LFODepth" 0}   Low Frequence Oscillator phase modulations Depth
    @{"LFOPhDiff" link "FlangerLFOPhDiff" 0}   Low Frequence Oscillator Phase Difference
    @{"L/R Depth" link "L/RDepth" 0}   Left to Right distance (Depth)
    @{"PDir:    " link "PDir" 0}   Panorama Direction
    @{"PM Depth " link "PM Depth" 0}   Frequence Modulation Depth (P ?? ... )
    @{"SndVxtoRv" link "SENDFXTOREVERB" 0}   Send Variationseffect to Reverb
    @{"SndVxtoCh" link "SENDFXTOCHORUS" 0}   Send Variationseffect to Chorus
    @{"VarPan   " link "VarPan" 0}   Variationseffect Panorama
    @{"VarReturn" link "VarReturn" 0}   Variationseffect Return
@endnode

@node "F/RDepth" "Front to Rear depth (distance)"

    @{b}@{u}Front to Rear depth (distance)@{uu}@{ub}



@endnode

@node "L/RDepth" "Left to Right Depth (distance)"

    @{b}@{u}Left to Right Depth (distance)@{uu}@{ub}

@endnode

@node "PDir" "Panorama Direction"

    @{b}@{u}Panorama Direction@{uu}@{ub}

    There are 6 possibilitys:

    The red names:

    L<>R    in the same time to left and right
            like a swinging mono-stereo

    L>R     in beginns to swing to left and then to right
            try it with a low LFO speed

    R>L     the same in the other direction

    Ltrn    Left turn - beginns left and swing
        
    Rtrn    Right turn - beginns right and swing

    L.R     it does not swing between left and right
            it's like switching between left and right
@endnode

@node "PM Depth" "Phase Modulation Depth"

    @{b}@{u}Phase Modulation Depth@{uu}@{ub}

    The label PM Depth is not correct.

    This is the Frequence Modulations Depth, you can influence.

@endnode

